{"award_age":50.0,"bio_image":"full\/a903a51876dbe851e7ed0eeb130c72dc9a87133e.jpg","category":"Physiology or Medicine","country":"United Kingdom","date_of_birth":"1943-09-06T00:00:00.000Z","date_of_death":null,"gender":"male","image_urls":["http:\/\/upload.wikimedia.org\/wikipedia\/commons\/thumb\/1\/19\/Roberts%2C_Richard_John_%281943%29.jpg\/220px-Roberts%2C_Richard_John_%281943%29.jpg"],"link":"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Richard_J._Roberts","mini_bio":"<p><b>Sir Richard \"Rich\" John Roberts<\/b> (born 6 September 1943) is an <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/English_people\" title=\"English people\">English<\/a> <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Biochemist\" title=\"Biochemist\">biochemist<\/a> and <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Molecular_biology\" title=\"Molecular biology\">molecular biologist<\/a>. He was awarded the 1993 <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Nobel_Prize_in_Physiology_or_Medicine\" title=\"Nobel Prize in Physiology or Medicine\">Nobel Prize in Physiology or Medicine<\/a> with <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Phillip_Allen_Sharp\" title=\"Phillip Allen Sharp\">Phillip Allen Sharp<\/a> for the discovery of <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Intron\" title=\"Intron\">introns<\/a> in <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Eukaryote\" title=\"Eukaryote\">eukaryotic<\/a> <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/DNA\" title=\"DNA\">DNA<\/a> and the mechanism of gene-splicing. He currently works at <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/New_England_Biolabs\" title=\"New England Biolabs\">New England Biolabs<\/a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-8\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Richard_J._Roberts#cite_note-8\"><span>[<\/span>8<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-9\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Richard_J._Roberts#cite_note-9\"><span>[<\/span>9<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup><\/p><p>Roberts was born in <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Derby\" title=\"Derby\">Derby<\/a>, the son of Edna (Allsop) and John Roberts, an auto mechanic.<sup id=\"cite_ref-10\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Richard_J._Roberts#cite_note-10\"><span>[<\/span>10<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup> When he was four, Roberts' family moved to <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Bath,_Somerset\" title=\"Bath, Somerset\">Bath<\/a>. In Bath, he attended <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/City_of_Bath_Boys%27_School\" title=\"City of Bath Boys' School\" class=\"mw-redirect\">City of Bath Boys' School<\/a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-11\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Richard_J._Roberts#cite_note-11\"><span>[<\/span>11<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup> As a child he at first wanted to be a <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Detective\" title=\"Detective\">detective<\/a> and then, when given a <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Chemistry_set\" title=\"Chemistry set\">chemistry set<\/a>, a <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Chemist\" title=\"Chemist\">chemist<\/a>.<\/p><p>He graduated from the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/University_of_Sheffield\" title=\"University of Sheffield\">University of Sheffield<\/a> in 1965 with a <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Bachelor_of_Science\" title=\"Bachelor of Science\">Bachelor of Science<\/a> degree in <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Chemistry\" title=\"Chemistry\">Chemistry<\/a> and a <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/PhD\" title=\"PhD\" class=\"mw-redirect\">PhD<\/a> in 1969.<sup id=\"cite_ref-whoswho_1-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Richard_J._Roberts#cite_note-whoswho-1\"><span>[<\/span>1<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup> His thesis involved <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Phytochemical\" title=\"Phytochemical\">phytochemical<\/a> studies of <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Neoflavonoid\" title=\"Neoflavonoid\">neoflavonoids<\/a> and <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Isoflavonoid\" title=\"Isoflavonoid\">isoflavonoids<\/a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-robertsphd_7-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Richard_J._Roberts#cite_note-robertsphd-7\"><span>[<\/span>7<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup><\/p><p>After becoming a Nobel Laureate in 1993 he was awarded an Honorary Degree (Doctor of Science) by the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/University_of_Bath\" title=\"University of Bath\">University of Bath<\/a> in 1994.<sup id=\"cite_ref-12\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Richard_J._Roberts#cite_note-12\"><span>[<\/span>12<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup><\/p><p>In 2005, a multi-million pound expansion to the chemistry department at the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/University_of_Sheffield\" title=\"University of Sheffield\">University of Sheffield<\/a>, where he had been a student, was named after him. A refurbished science department at <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Beechen_Cliff_School\" title=\"Beechen Cliff School\">Beechen Cliff School<\/a> (previously City of Bath Boys' School) was also named after Roberts, who had donated a substantial sum of his Nobel prize winnings to the school.<sup id=\"cite_ref-13\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Richard_J._Roberts#cite_note-13\"><span>[<\/span>13<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup><\/p><p>Roberts was one of the signers of the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Humanist_Manifesto_II\" title=\"Humanist Manifesto II\">Humanist Manifesto<\/a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-14\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Richard_J._Roberts#cite_note-14\"><span>[<\/span>14<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup> He was <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Knight_Bachelor\" title=\"Knight Bachelor\">knighted<\/a> in the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/2008_Birthday_Honours\" title=\"2008 Birthday Honours\">2008 Birthday Honours<\/a>.<\/p><p>Roberts is a member of the Advisory Board of <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Patient-innovation.com\" title=\"Patient-innovation.com\">Patient Innovation<\/a>, a nonprofit, international, multilingual, free venue for patients and caregivers of any disease to share their innovations.<\/p>","name":"Richard J. Roberts","place_of_birth":"Derby , England, UK","place_of_death":null,"text":"Richard J. Roberts , Physiology or Medicine, 1993","year":1993.0}